<div id="review_2590996215" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2590996215" />
    <a title="Armin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58913296-armin"><img alt="Armin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1584015407p2/58913296.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2590996215?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Armin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Armin" href="/user/show/58913296-armin">Armin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9782253098393" href="/book/show/810919.La_Chanson_de_Roland">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58913296-armin?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58913296-armin?shelf=french">french</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58913296-armin?shelf=chevaleresque">chevaleresque</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2590996215" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3187193845628439578">It was the first time I was reading a Chanson de Geste, or any other kind of early Romance literature from the period that the national literatures were coming into existence.<br/>The book is an epic narrative of Charlemagne’s campaign in Spain against the Saracens and how he was betrayed by one of his advisors, thereby losing Roland, aka “his right arm.”<br/>In case you are not familiar with this kind of texts, they highlight the grandeur of Christianity and lashes out at other faiths (namely Islam) call</span>
  <span id="freeText3187193845628439578" style="display:none">It was the first time I was reading a Chanson de Geste, or any other kind of early Romance literature from the period that the national literatures were coming into existence.<br />The book is an epic narrative of Charlemagne’s campaign in Spain against the Saracens and how he was betrayed by one of his advisors, thereby losing Roland, aka “his right arm.”<br />In case you are not familiar with this kind of texts, they highlight the grandeur of Christianity and lashes out at other faiths (namely Islam) calling them simply heresy. They emphasize the importance of chivalry and the role of knights and the reciprocal commitments of knights and Lord and how the earthly King (Charlemagne in this case) is treated as the effective trace of Father and Son on Earth. We also see other types of characters which are quite recurring in this sort of literature; the cultred woman, the old man who has been in the court for long but appears treasonous and the knights who all gather specifically around one single knight.<br />It was a great pleasure reading this book in French; now off to the next one: Chrétien de Troyes!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3187193845628439578" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


