<div id="review_2562229581" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2562229581" />
    <a title="Reading Through the Lists" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16249298-reading-through-the-lists"><img alt="Reading Through the Lists" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1589045294p2/16249298.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2562229581?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Reading Through the Lists" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Reading Through the Lists" href="/user/show/16249298-reading-through-the-lists">Reading Through the Lists</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140445329" href="/book/show/763841.The_Song_of_Roland">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2562229581" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10033074656005775089">“Roland is brave and Oliver is wise;<br/>Both are marvelous vassals.” <br/><br/>This is now my fourth time reading <i>The Song of Roland</i>, and, as with most books I teach, I have come to appreciate it precisely for its context, inaccuracies, and beliefs. <br/><br/>There’s so much to talk about: the mirroring of the Muslims and Christians, the Crusade rhetoric, the role of the good vassal, pride vs. wisdom. But the emotional through-line of the story for me will always be Roland and Oliver--their friendship, their differing </span>
  <span id="freeText10033074656005775089" style="display:none">“Roland is brave and Oliver is wise;<br />Both are marvelous vassals.” <br /><br />This is now my fourth time reading <i>The Song of Roland</i>, and, as with most books I teach, I have come to appreciate it precisely for its context, inaccuracies, and beliefs. <br /><br />There’s so much to talk about: the mirroring of the Muslims and Christians, the Crusade rhetoric, the role of the good vassal, pride vs. wisdom. But the emotional through-line of the story for me will always be Roland and Oliver--their friendship, their differing personalities, their love for each other. There’s a lot of shameless pathos in <i>The Song of Roland</i> (copious weeping, fainting, and groaning); you can’t not feel something while reading. I do, every time. <br /><br />5 stars. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10033074656005775089" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


