  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2164164265?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="May Ling" class="user" itemprop="url" name="May Ling" href="/user/show/1667021-may-ling">May Ling</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140440751" href="/book/show/103390.The_Song_of_Roland">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1667021-may-ling?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2164164265" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18418380534990720639">Got it from my free laundry room book exchange. <br/>I always have to give the translator credit for trying to not only translate from old french to modern english, but also keep the rhyming concept and feel. Difficult, but achieved in this piece, IMO. If you are looking for a scholars opinion, though I might not be the right person.<br/><br/>As for the story itself, I think it&apos;s interesting to see how times have changed. What constitutes rage. The emotions are simple and the reasons are pure. Nice. The prefac</span>
  <span id="freeText18418380534990720639" style="display:none">Got it from my free laundry room book exchange. <br />I always have to give the translator credit for trying to not only translate from old french to modern english, but also keep the rhyming concept and feel. Difficult, but achieved in this piece, IMO. If you are looking for a scholars opinion, though I might not be the right person.<br /><br />As for the story itself, I think it's interesting to see how times have changed. What constitutes rage. The emotions are simple and the reasons are pure. Nice. The preface was great at explaining what one should look out for in the way of imagery. I'm not in grade school anymore, so I prefer to read knowing a bit more what I'm looking at in advance so I can appreciate it. If you hate that, don't read the preface first. <br /><br />Cool. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18418380534990720639" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

